A deployed Entrust KeyControl v5.4 cluster (Click this sentence to learn how to do this) vCenter and ESXi Host(s) running vSphere 7.x or higher Trusted connection between Entrust KeyControl and vCenter (Click this sentence to learn how to do this) Powered-off VM Now, let&rsquo;s get started&hellip;
Select a VM to Encrypt Right click a VM and select VM Policies, Edit VM Storage Policies

